Please translate each line literally into English.
1 Per correr miglior acque alza le vele 2 omai la navicella del mio ingegno, 3 che lascia dietro a sé mar sì crudele;
4 e canterò di quel secondo regno 5 dove l’umano spirito si purga 6 e di salire al ciel diventa degno.

query.result:
58 This one never saw the last evening;
59 but through his folly it was so near to him,
60 that very little time was to turn [around].

64 I have shown him all the hostile people;
65 and now I intend to show those spirits
66 who purge themselves under your dominion.

67 How I have led him would be long to tell you;
68 from above descends virtue that helps me
69 to lead him to see you and to hear you.

76 The eternal decrees are not damaged for us,
77 because this one lives and Minos does not bind me;
78 but I am of the circle where are the chaste eyes

79 of your Marcia, who even now prays to you in sight,
80 oh holy breast, that holds it for you;
81 through her love therefore bend to us.

82 Let me leave to go through your seven kingdoms;
83 I will bring thanks from her to you,
84 if worthy to be mentioned down there.

